Maggie is a 93-year-old widow (used to be an elementary school teacher) who has lived a modest and financially responsible life. 
She receives income from Social Security, a teacher’s pension, and retirement savings. 
While she is not highly tech-savvy, she owns a tablet that she uses for email, video calls with family, and basic browsing. 
Her grandson helped her download the financial tracking app.

She values independence and wants to remain in control of her finances without relying entirely on her children.
She want to be able to easiler monitor retirement funds to ensure they last, save and organize mopney she hopes to pass on to her grandchildren, and avoid scam charges. 

*Low to moderate technology comfort level

User Stories:

As a user that isn't super confident in technology, I want a system that is very easy to use and understand with clear instructions.
As an aging user, I want the ability to increase the size of the text so that I can easily read it.
As someone concerned about fraud, I want to easily spot unfamiliar or unusual charges, so that I can avoid scam-related losses.

User Scenario:

Maggie, a 93-year-old retired teacher, sits down in the evening with her tablet to review her finances. 
She opens the financial tracking app that her grandson helped install and logs in. 
The app displays a simple dashboard with large, easy-to-read text, showing her Social Security deposits, pension income, and recent expenses.
While reviewing the dashboard, Maggie notices an alert about an unusual charge on her account. The app clearly highlights the transaction and provides simple instructions on what to do next. 
After reviewing it, she feels reassured that she can keep track of her money and spot potential scams.
Before closing the app, Maggie quickly checks how much money she has set aside in savings for her grandchildren without getting lost in the weeds with clutter and features that don't matter to her. 
Feeling confident that her finances are organized and secure, she puts down her tablet and continues her evening.

Wants: 
- Large readable text
- Simple dashboard showing only the things she needs
- Alerts for unusual activity
